properties.summary: Attack on madrassa and alleged Taliban/altoQaeda training camp run by Maulvi Liaqat (killed). Up to 82 killed, almost all of them children.

Strike on house and mosque allegedly kills Abu Sulayman Jazairi, altoQaeda weapons expert (actually killed April 2009). Up to 18 die including 4to11 militants. Claims that women and children also died. Pakistan's PM condemns attack.

Main target Ayman altoZawahiri absent at supposed altoQaeda/Taliban commanders meeting in Damadola, Bajaur. Despite inital reports that all victims were altoQaeda or Taliban, including six commanders, later transpires all dead were civilians.
properties.target: Ayman altoZawahiri; Abu Khabab altoMasri; Abd Rahman altoMasri altoMaghribi; Abu Ubeidah altoMasri; Marwan altoSuri; Khalid Habib; Abdul Hadi altoIraqi

properties.summary: Attack on TTP deputy leader Maulvi Faqir misses him by minutes. 27 killed and 8 injured. Pakistan denies drone involvement.

7 alleged militants killed in attack in Tirah valley, Khyber Agency.  Truck destroyed. Dead said to be from Swat Taliban (commander Ibne Amin reportedly killed) and Bahadur?s group. Local houses also damaged.
CIA drone used in Pakistani seizure of al Qaeda's Zabu ul Taifi. First known drone use of Obama presidency (day two) shows close secret link between countries.
House and two trucks attacked in first known strike in Khyber Agency. 15 killed. Local TTP commander Gul Saeed reported among dead.
Multiple strikes on a TTP compound in Barjo, Kurram Agency kill 25to31 and injure up to 50. Taliban hostages also possibly among dead. CIA later briefs Pakistan on attack.

3rd strike of day in Khyber Agency kills up to 32 alleged Lashkar e Islam members when houses in Speen Drang destroyed. Ali Marjan, Yar Azam and Mehmud local LeI commanders, and Ibne Amin, altoQaeda linked Swat Taliban subtoleader, reported dead.
Attack on compound in Naqai/ Narai kills 11to15 alleged Swat Taliban and injures 2.
First of triple strikes in Khyber Agency. Two cars destroyed in Sandana, 7 alleged TTP militants killed, 7to11 injured.
Two vehicles 'recently crossed from Afghanistan' destroyed in rare Kurram Agency attack. 6 alleged Haqqani Network (or TTP) militants killed.
Attack on day of local peace deal signing kills 31 (Taliban says 24 fighters killed) and injures 20to50 in Sarpal, Kurram Agency at [alleged] TTP camp.
Up to 10 civilians killed and 4to5 militants in attack on TTP in Khadezai, Orakzai Agency (first known attack here). CIA later briefs Pakistan on strike.
Failed attack on unnamed altoQaeda official by CIA drone. Eight locals killed including two women and two children. Report that 'US soldiers' take away tribesmen following strike.
Local Taliban commander Abdur Rehman reported killed in strike in Saigdai, North Waziristan which kills up to 12 more people and injures 3.
7 killed in first of triple strike in Kurram Agency. 5 initially die in Noor Alam when car destroyed. As locals attempted aid, drones kill a further 2.
In 2nd of 3 strikes in Kurram, house struck and 3to5 alleged militants killed in Noor Alam. Dead said to be Afghans.
Strike in Badshah Kot, Kurram Agency destroys a residential compound. No casualty figure available.
Eight killed and 12 injured in attack on compound and vehicle in Datta Khel, North Waziristan.
Housing compound of Awar Gul ?completely destroyed? in Datta Khel, North Waziristan.  At least 10 alleged militants killed, 4 injured.
5 killed, including two women and a child, in strike in Datta Khel, North Waziristan.
13to14 killed, including reported villagers, in double attack on vehicles and houses in Doga, Datta Khel, North Waziristan.
Attack on Datta Khel in North Waziristan kills 5 alleged militants and injures 2to3.
Two killed in 4am attack on car at Gadda Maramay, Datta Khel, North Waziristan. Three nearby houses damaged ? further casualties unknown.

Up to 53 people killed ? mostly civilians ? in strike on car and tribal meeting in Datta Khel area. Pakistan?s President, Prime Minister and Army chief condemn US. Sharabat Khan, listed among dead, claimed as either a Bahadur commander or mine contractor.
4to5 alleged militants killed and ?scores? injured when car destroyed in Datta Khel, North Waziristan.
10to11 killed including 8 al Qaeda and 2 injured in attack on Datta Khel, North Waziristan.
Al Qaeda?s operational commander in Pakistan, Shaikh altoFatah, aka Abdul Razzak, killed along with Haji Niaz,  Naimatullah and 1 other when car destroyed near Miranshah, North Waziristan.
Car attacked in Datta Khel, North Waziristan and 4to5 alleged militants killed. Strike confused at time with Ob 183.
Attack kills 4to5 alleged militants in Datta Khel, North Waziristan when either a housing compound or car was attacked.
Attack hits ammunition store at Taliban camp, damaging nearby houses. 4 children and 3 women among 13 dead. Dattakhel, Miramshah, North Waziristan.
6 drones attack a picktoup van (and possibly house) in Datta Khel, North Waziristan. 5to8 alleged militants killed, 1 injured, including ?foreigners?.
Conflicting accounts suggest a car or compound attacked, with 2to4 killed and 'a few others' injured. Datta Khel, North Waziristan.
Triple linked strike over an hour on house and car kills 11 alleged militants, including ?3 foreigners?. Datta Khel, North Waziristan. At least 2 rescuers killed.
Attack on house and madrassa in Danda Saigdai kills 4 and injures 3. Locals deny the dead were bombtomaking militants to and names them as Zahidullah, Abdul Ghafoor, Jan Mohammed Mehsud and Dilawar.
A ?white car? destroyed in Ghoroski, North Waziristan. Four alleged militant victims reported to be from South Waziristan.
Attack kills 2to3 alleged militants on motorbike, and kills others attempting rescue. Darazinda, North Waziristan.
In first of 3 linked strikes, drones attack two alleged militant houses in Ghulam Khan, North Waziristan.  5to6 killed,  ?some? injured. Al Qaeda?s Nasir altoWahishi wrongly reported killed.
After waiting up to 3 hours locals attempt to retrieve dead from Ob175. Drones attack again, killing 4to12.
Fighters returning on foot from Afghanistan are alleged targets in strike in Ghulam Khan, North Waziristan. 5to6 killed.
9 killed and others injured in joint strike by 8 drones on house and car in Ghulam Khan, North Waziristan. Taliban kill 3 ?drone spies? nearby.
In final of 3 linked strikes, truck allegedly carrying wounded of Ob 175/ 176 attacked. Two other vehicles also struck carrying alleged militants. 9to10 reported killed.
4to8 killed after allegedly returning from a raid in Afghanistan. Ghulam Khan, North Waziristan. Vehicle destroyed.
Mass grave needed after 20 killed, including ?women and children? in attack on vehicle and house in Ghulam Khan, North Waziristan.
8to13 killed and 6 injured, including 5 civilians and  ?3 foreign fighters? in attack on house and car in Dargi Mandi. TTP leader Mohammad Qari Zaffar falsely reported dead.
Ten killed at alleged Taliban compound in attack on Dargmandi, Miram Shah, North Waziristan.

Around 10 civilians including 4 women and 3 children killed in attack on alleged  Haqqani Network compound,  Darga Mandi, North Waziristan. CIA source later claims Agency changes rules after attack to limit civilian deaths.
Alleged Taliban compound in Derga mandai, North Waziristan attacked. 5 killed, 3 injured.
Villagers flee in panic as multiple drones attack two housing compounds before dawn, killing at least 14, reportedly including civilian rescuers. Dargha Mandi, North Waziristan.
Seven 'AQ/ Taliban' among 12to14 killed including 3 women and 4 children. Gurwak, North Waziristan.
Attack on car and house in Mandi Khel, North Waziristan kills 7to9 alleged militants. See Ob181.
Attack on house kills 4to7 people, who some allege are militants. Tabbi, North Waziristan.
Four children and 6 alleged Haqqani Network militants killed in first of two attacks of day  on Dandy Darpa Khel area, North Waziristan. Two houses destroyed.

10 or more killed in fresh attack on Danda Darpa Khel.  British 'Taliban supporter' Abdul Jabbar and 8 alleged German militants later reported  dead along with Uzbek commander 'Qureshi'. Al Qaeda's Fahd Mohammad Ahmed altoQuso emerges alive December 2010.
After waiting two hours, rescuers attempt to retrieve dead and injured at destroyed Mandi Khel house but are attacked. 4to6 killed.
Mohammed Haqqani killed in Dandy Darpa Khel, North Waziristan, with 3 others. US intel official later boasts: ? We were gunning for Siraj but got his little brother instead?.
Attack on Haqqani Network kills 7 and injures 6 in Danda Darpakhel, North Waziristan.
4 children and 2 women reported among dead after attack in Mohammad Khel, North Waziristan.  Al Qaeda later says its chief finance official Mustafa Abu Yazid died.
Compound ?of local militant commander Tariq Khan? attacked. At least 9 of 13 killed reportedly civilians.
In fourth strike of day another vehicle struck in Boya or Mohammad Khel, North Waziristan. 4 alleged militants killed.
Attack on seminary linked to Haqqani Network kills ten (including 7 students) and wounds 11 in Danda Darpakhel, Miramshah, North Waziristan.
Attack on alleged Haqqani Network compound kills 4 and injures 7 in Danda Darpa Khel, North Waziristan.
6 killed, 4 injured  in attack on car and house/ seminary in Tabbi (Tappi?) Torkhel, North Waziristan.  Some reports claim Taliban commander Hamza Mehsud killed.
Two vehicles were hit in an early monring strike, killing at least 4. The vehicles were reportedly traveling from Miranshah.

Badruddin Haqqani, the network's senior military commander and son of its founder, was killed when up to 25 dided in a 7pm strike. Haqqani's son Osama may also have perished when drones hit a car and vehicle
4 reported killed in attack on truck in Shawal area, South Waziristan.
11to12 killed and 4 injured in attack on alleged Haqqani Network housing compound. Bushnarai.
5 killed in attack on house/ compound in Charkhel, North Waziristan. 4 ?Turkmen fighters? possibly among dead.
6to12 killed in attack on truck in Shawal, North Waziristan. 3 ?foreigners? reported among alleged militants.
Drones kill al Qaeda logistician Abu Wafa al Qsaudi along with 4to6 others (reported as all Arabs) in attack on Momadkhel, North Waziristan.
Car hit in attack on alleged militants in Dwa Tooe, Datta Khel. Restaurant and house also caught in blast. 12to17 killed, including civilian(s).
Strike on alleged ?militant hideout? in Shanakhora, Miranshah, North Waziristan kills 4 and wounds 5.
Five alleged militants killed and 3 injured in attack on Payakhel, North Waziristan.
Bazaar in Miranshah attacked.  Hussein altoYemeni, linked to attack on CIA base, killed along with 8 other alleged al Qaeda.
Miram Shah house attacked in North Waziristan, killing 5 and wounding 2. No further details known.
Target Abu Hamza Rabia (altoQaeda) killed along with 4 others including an 8toyeartoold and a 17toyeartoold, Rabia's son.
Car and motorbike destroyed and 5to6 alleged militants killed in Kaisore, North Waziristan.
Double strike on vehicle and rescuers in Khaisoor, North Waziristan kills at least 6 ? locals say all are civilians.
4to5 killed in car in Tappi, North Waziristan including   Abdul Haq altoTurkistani, leader of militant group the Turkistani Islamic Party.
2 cars attacked in Hamzoni, North Waziristan, killing 5 and injuring 4.  Nearby house damaged. ?Foreigners? reported among dead.
4 alleged militants killed in their car by strike in Ambar Shaga, North Waziristan.
Six alleged Uzbek  militants killed, 5 injured in attack near Miranshah, North Waziristan.
Mohammad Usman reported dead (killed again June 2011) along with up to 4 others. 4 injured. House and car attacked. Miranshah, North Waziristan.
Jeep destroyed and 3to5 alleged militants killed in attack west of Miranshah, North Waziristan. 6to7 drones involved in attack.
Six killed including militants, woman and little girl; 8 injured. CIA claims ?two [unnamed] prominent al Qaeda paramilitary commanders? die.  Tappi/ Ghundi village near Miram Shah, North Waziristan.
4to6 alleged militants killed when their car destroyed in Tappi, North Waziristan.
Car destroyed in attack on alleged militants in Miranshah, North Waziristan. 4 killed.  Reports that all dead are actually civilians.
25to29, mostly ?local tribesmen? killed in attack on madrasa and vehicle in Kaisore, Miram Shah, North Waziristan. Two Arabs reported among dead, including Asad altoMisri.
21 die, including women and 6 children, in attack on madrassa linked to Haqqani family. Dandy Darpa Khel, Miranshah, North Waziristan.

Attack on Tol Khel, North Waziristan kills 12 'rebel fighters' of local altoBadr group and wounds 14. CIA secretly claims ?a Predator killed 10 to 15 militants associated with Al Qaeda facilitator Qari Imran?s training camp.?
First recorded attack on the Haqqani network (involved in attacks on US forces in Afghanistan) kills at least 5 probably militants and wounds 6to12.

Major strike kills Abu Haris, AQ chief in Pakistan, Saudis Abdullah and Abu Hamza; Zain Ul Abu Qasim aka Hakaimi, Egyptian AQ chief) and 21 others including eight grandchildren, 2 wives, sister, sistertointolaw and other relatives of Jalaluddin Haqqani.  Da
Drones return during funeral of Niaz Wali and kill approximately 85, including up to 50 civilians (10 children and 4 tribal leaders.) Dead buried in mass grave. Baitullah Mehsud escapes.
Between 6 and 9 killed and 3 wounded in attack on alleged militants in  house in Miranshah, North Waziristan.
At least 5 people killed as tribesmen gathered for Eid, declared early in Waziristan. One named militant was killed, and his wife. A house and car were hit in the attack.
House and vehicle destroyed. 5 alleged militants of Hafiz Gul Bahadur?s faction killed, 3 injured in Tappi, North Waziristan.
Six killed and 2 injured in attack on alleged militants at a former school. Tappi, North Waziristan.
4 ?foreign militants? killed, 1 injured after pulling over car to pray. Angar Shaga, North Waziristan.
Failed strike against Abu Hamza Rabia (altoQaeda's No.3) destroys his house and kills 8, including Rabia's wife and children including young daughter.
4 killed and 2 injured at Taliban guesttohouse, Tapi Khel, North Waziristan.  Al Qaeda?s Shaikh Mansoor among dead.
3to7 alleged militants killed in attack on house/ compound near Datta Khel, North Waziristan. 3 injured.
Car and nearby house struck in Mohammad Khel, North Waziristan. Two Turkmenistan ?militants? said to be among 5to7 killed.
3to5 alleged militants killed in attack on car in Doga Mada Khel, North Waziristan.
Up to 14 killed, including ?many civilians? according to elders in one report, in strike on house in Sheerani, North Waziristan.
7to9 killed and ?several? injured in attack on alleged militant house in Machi Khel, North Waziristan.
Vehicle destroyed and 4to5 alleged militants reported killed in Machi Khel, North Waziristan. No further details known.
16 alleged 'foreign militants' from al Badr group killed in Datta Khel, North Waziristan.
Strike in Muhammad Khel, reportedly against locals firing on nearby swarm of drones. Casualties unknown.
Truck destroyed and explodes in or near village of Malik Jashdar, North Waziristan. 3to5 killed including 2 ?Arabs?.
House and motorbike  attacked in Ghar Laley, North Waziristan. 4to6 alleged militants killed.
House of Alif Deen  (killed) attacked as body from Ob 153 was being brought into compound. 5to8 killed including ?Arabs?.  Ismail Khan, North Waziristan.
At least 8 people killed and 12 injured in attack on Madakhel, North Waziristan, including rescuers in return drone strike.
Uzbek militant Tahir Yuldashev allegedly killed with 7 others in attack at Tapar Ghai, Kanigram, South Waziristan. His militant IMU group deny death for more than a year.
North Waziristan Taliban commander Haji Omar reported killed along with 3to6 others, some civilians, in Mir Ali. Owner of house whose son (and wife?) dies later sues CIA.
Vehicle attacked in Mir Ali, North Waziristan. German militant Eric Breininger, alias Abdul Gaffar eltoAlmani  among 6 dead.  House also damaged.
Strike in Datta Khel, North Waziristan kills 13 and injures 12.  Two houses destroyed.
Four killed in attack on Mohammad Khel, North Waziristan. No other details known.
5to8 killed in attack on alleged militant compound near Lowari  Mandi, North Waziristan.
Car destroyed and nearby house badly damaged, 4 alleged militants killed, in Doga Mada Khel, North Waziristan.
Palestinian Jamal Saeed Abdul Rahim ? linked to a deadly 1986 air hijack ? killed with up to 12 others in Ismail Khel, North Waziristan including al Qaeda bodyguard Mansur al Shami.
10 killed and 12 wounded in attack on alleged militant training compound, Machi Khel, North Waziristan.

Attack aimed at meeting of al Qaeda and Taliban leaders kills 9 including wife and children of local Taliban commander Hafiz Sahar Gul. Tati, Miram Shah, North Waziristan. Claims that ISI warned those at meeting to flee.
5 killed, including 2 ?foreigners? in attack on alleged Hafiz Gul Bahadur compound. Mada Khel, North Waziristan.
In second attack on a car in one day, at least 2 people killed in Sherani, North Waziristan.
Related attack kills 7 as fleeing vehicles struck in Mizar Madakhel area.
9 ? 15 killed, including 4 Arabs, 2 Uzbeks, local militants, it?s alleged. Muhammad Khel, North Waziristan.
3to6 alleged militants killed in attack on picktoup truck in Aimarki area of Mir Ali, North Waziristan.
Three alleged militants killed and 3to4 injured in Ghundikala, North Waziristan. Car destroyed.
Motorcycle destroyed in town of Doga Mada Khel, North Waziristan.  3 killed, 1 possibly a ?foreigner?.
House and car destroyed in Mosaki, North Waziristan.  Five killed including up to 3 ?Arabs?, local teacher Sadiq Noor (allegedly linked to militants) and his 9toyear old son Wajid.
7to15 alleged militants killed and ?4 injured in attack on car or house, Gorwek, North Waziristan.
Art student Sanaullah killed with 3 college friends, car destroyed, Pir Keley, North Waziristan.
6 killed, including TTP ?suicide bombing mastermind? Qari Hussain, killed in strike on house in Asar, Datta Khel, North Waziristan. US still keeps Hussain on its Wanted list.
Double strike in vicinity of Afghan refugee camp in Shiva, Mir Ali, North Waziristan kills up to 9 and injures 3.
Attack during Ramadan prayers kills TTP local commander Amir Movia and other alleged militants. Nearby house also hit. 13 killed and 5 injured at Issori, North Waziristan.
Attack on madrassa in Mami Rogha kills 30to34 with 18 'foreigners' (Chechen, Uzbek and Arab) reported among dead. Some suggestion children also killed.
Vehicles and compound destroyed. 8to9 alleged militants killed. Norak, Miransha, North Waziristan.
3 killed (later claimed as al Qaeda?s Sheikh Ihsanullah; Abu Ibrahim,  a commander of the FursantoitoMohammed Group; and an unnamed Turkish foreign fighter). Khaddi or Norak, North Waziristan.
5 ?Uzbek fighters ? reported killed in first of 3 strikes. Car destroyed, Qutab Khel, North Waziristan.
Double strike on house and car in Inzarkas, North Waziristan kills 8 alleged militants.
Rescuers (described as either villagers and militants) of Ob55 attacked as they search for survivors.  At least 5 killed. Datta Khel, North Waziristan.
Seven alleged militants killed including 'two Arabs'  in attack on Newey Adda, North Waziristan.
4to10 killed and 2 injured in attack on house/ compound in Sandasa, Mir Ali, North Waziristan. Some reports claim dead are foreigners.
Target Haitham altoYemeni (altoQaeda explosives expert) and unknown car passenger killed.
Attack destroys car and targets rescuers in Toor Khel, North Waziristan. 6 killed and 22 injured. Drones give chase to escaping car.
3to5 women and 4to5 children among 25 reported killed in attack at Spinwan [Afghan refugee camp], North Waziristan.
Attack on house of [Prof] Taj Mohammad in Chashma, Miram Shah, North Waziristan kills three, possibly civilians.
12 killed, 5 injured in initial strike on alleged militant compound in Datta Khel, North Waziristan.
Double strike on house and car in Sanzali, North Waziristan kills ?at least? seven. Six injured. ?Foreigners? said to be among dead.
Drone misses vehicle in first strike, allowing 4 occupants to escape on foot. Or drone kills 3to4. Hassan Khel, North Waziristan.
Home of ?local militant? Musharaf Gul bombed and 6 killed, 8 injured. Norak, Mir Ali, North Waziristan.
4 alleged Haqqani militants killed as car destroyed  in Qutabkhel, North Waziristan. Commander Saifullah Haqqani later reported among dead.
Six killed and two injured in attack on two cars in Kutabkhel, North Waziristan. Claims that all dead are civilians and target had left area.
Vehicle destroyed and 3to4 alleged militants killed in Naurak, North Waziristan.
Attack destroys car in Toori Khel, North Waziristan: explosion heard 15 miles away. Five die including IMU leader Najmiddin Kamolitdinovic. Ilyas Kashmiri wrongly claimed dead 2nd time in a week.
Attack on alleged Taliban attending funeral prayers for victims of Ob49. Wazgai, Datta Khel, North Waziristan. 8 killed, 5 wounded.
Alleged militant compound attacked in Machis, North Waziristan. 6 killed, 3 injured.
Rashid Rauf, British Al Qaeda and suspect in 2006 planes plot, possibly killed alongside Egyptian explosives expert Abu Zubair altoMasri and three others. Ali Khel, Miram Shah, North Waziristan.
Strike in Tapi Tool, Miran Sha, North Waziristan kills two, injures 3.
Abdur Rehman?s house in Khaddi, North Waziristan attacked along with car. 6to9 reported killed including ?Mustafa?, militant leader and 2 ?foreigners?.
Attack in Mir Ali, North Waziristan allegedly kills al Qaeda propaganda boss Abu Jihad al Masri and Abu Kasha (still alive). Up to 19 civilians also die.
properties.target: Abu Jihad altoMasri; Abdur Rehman abu Akash

properties.summary: Four alleged militants killed and 2 injured in attack on house in Lawra Mandi, Datta Khel.
Compound of Zafar Khan attacked in Haider Khel, North Waziristan.  3to5 alleged militants killed (possibly ?foreigners?), up to 15 injured.
Al Qaeda?s Atiyah Abd altoRahman reported killed in Mir Ali, North Waziristan. Qari Hussain Mehsud, deputy chief of TTP, again reported dead. Car and house attacked. Khaisoori, North Waziristan.
Compound of Ahmad Ali attacked in Haider Khel, North Waziristan. At least 6 alleged militants killed, 2 injured.
After tribesmen fire on three drones circling village of Toorikhel, North Waziristan, drone attack  kills 8, wounds 9.
2to4 alleged militants killed in attack on house in Khushali Toorikhel, North Waziristan.
Up to 25 killed and vehicle destroyed in pretodawn strike. Miram Shah,
4 killed, including possibly 3to4 civilians, and 2 injured in a strike on a housing compound and vehicle. Miram Shah, North Waziristan.
4to6 killed and 4 injured. Danda Darpakhel, North Wazaristan.
3to4 alleged militants killed in strike on vehicle. Danda Darpakhel, North Waziristan.

An attack on an alleged militant housing compound near Miranshah in North Waziristan killed up to 3 people and injured 3 others, according to local officials. Dawn reported that the casualties were part of the Haqqani Network.
7 killed and 3to4 injured in strike on a house in Miram Shah.
4  alleged militants killed in a strike on a house near Miranshah. Aslam Awan (aka Abdullah Khorasani), a senior operations operative for al Qaeda  is believed to be among dead.
10 alleged militants killed and up to 12 injured a strike on a house near Miranshah.
Up to 8 killed, possibly 2 civilians, in a strike on a house near Miransha.  Badar Mansoor, a local Pakistani al Qaeda leader, and his wife and child are believed to be amongst dead.
6 alleged militants killed and up to 7 injured in a strike on a house near Spalga.
Up  to 8 alleged militants belived to be senoir commanders of a Taliban faction were killed and 2to4 injured in a strike on a vehicle.
A Miranshah house destroyed killing 4 alleged militants.
3to6 alleged militants killed and up to 3 injured on a strike on an extogirl's school in Miranshah.
3to4 alleged militants killed and 2 injured on a strike on bakery in Miransha bazaar.
Up to 4 suspected militants killed in a strike on a shop or house in Miranshah bazaar. AFP reports witness saying another instance of a followtoup strike.
CIA drone struck a house killing up to eight people. The strike came around 7am, reportedly destroying the house.
At least 9 were killed when up to 8 missiles hit a compound alleged to belong to local militant commander Sadiq Noor, an ally of Hafiz Gul Bahadur.
In last of 4 strikes, village of Toor Narai hit. Casualties unknown.
2to4 killed, 3 injured in attack on home of Hameedullah in Khushali Khel, North Waziristan. No further details known.
In 3rd strike of day, vehicle attacked in Pai Khel village and a further 4to5 alleged militants killed. No other details known.
6 alleged militants killed in attack on car in Khar Qamar area of North Waziristan.
Home of local Taliban leader Haleem Khan targeted. 6to8 killed, 3 injured. Khushali Toorkhel, North Waziristan. Khan survives.
2 British Muslim converts (Mr Stephen/ Abu Bakr and Mr Dearsmith/ Mansoor Ahmed) among 4 alleged militants killed in attack on car in Khadar Khel, North Waziristan.
4to6 killed in attack on alleged militant house in Aziz Khel, North Waziristan. Taliban?s Qari Hussain reported killed (again) by some.

Militant meeting inside water plant attacked. Nearby house rented from Malik Mir Sharof also destroyed. 13to17 killed, 18 injured.  Al Qaeda?s Sheikh Abu Ahmad later reported among dead. Militants confirm strike.
Named Western al Qaeda militant among six reported killed in strike on guesthouse in Mir Ali, North Waziristan.
4 alleged militants killed in Khushali Toori Khel, Mir Ali, North Waziristan.
4to7 killed, including 0to4 civilians, and 3 injured in strike on vehicle, Norak, North Waziristan.
4to5 killed and two injured in strike on 10th anniversary of 9to11. Hiroskhel, North Waziristan.
A second strike of the day on either a moving vehicle or a house in North Waziristan killed up to 6 alleged militants, according to Pakistani security officials.
4to6 killed, including possibly 3to4 civilians, in strike on veichle. Datte Khel, North Waziristan.
Attack on vehicle near the town of Mir Ali, North Waziristan killed up to 4 alleged militants.
Up to 15 alleged militants killed in a strike on a vehicle in Mir Ali.
Up tp 12 killed and 3 injured, mostly civilians, after a strike hit a house and a nearby mosque during morning prayers.
Up to 10 alleged militants killed and 4 injured in a double strike on a house in the village of Khassokhel.
2to4 alleged militants killed in a strike on a vehicle in Datta Khel.
Up to 18 alleged militants killed in a strike on a militant compound. Abu Yahya altoLibi, al Qaeda's effective number two, is believed to be amongst dead.
3to4 alleged militants killed in strike on car. Qutab Khel, North Waziristan.
House and vehicle attacked in Deegan, North Waziristan. 6 alleged militants killed.
2 alleged militants killed as car destroyed in Khushali, North Waziristan. When survivor flees into nearby shop, drone reportedly destroys store, killing him and 2 shopkeepers.
Home of Salim/ Qasim Khan Dawar destroyed in Hurmuz, Mir Ali, North Waziristan.  3to5 alleged militants killed.
4 alleged militants killed in a strike on a vehicle traveling east from Miranshah.
4 killed, 5 injured in attack on house in Hurmaz, North Waziristan.
Vehicle destroyed and 4 alleged Haqqani militants killed. 5 local welfare workers also reported dead. Deghan, Datta Khel, North Waziristan.
4 to 5 civilians killed and 5 wounded in Abu Kasha related attack in Sokhel, Mir Ali, North Waziristan.
Five drones cluster for mass strike to kill Sirajudin Haqqani (who is not there). House attacked and up to 25 killed in Daigan, Datta Khel area, North Waziristan. 1st of 4 attacks on this date.
Car destroyed and 4 alleged militants killed in Degan, Datta Khel, North Waziristan. 2 ?Arabs?, 2 ?Westerners? reportedly killed. No further details known.
Car attacked in Khaso Khel, North Waziristan. 4 alleged militants killed. House also hit.

Car destroyed and 4to6 killed on Mir AlitoMiranshah road. All (?) later shown to be civilians: Akram Shah (driver); Umar Khan, owner of an auto sparetoparts shop; Shahzada, a student and Tariq, who ran a medical store. Some reports say 2 further dead unident

Abu Laith altoLibi, senior altoQaeda figure, killed along with 12 others, including Abu Obeida Tawari altoObeidi, Abu Adel altoKuwaiti, and Abdel Ghaffar altoDarnawi (possibly including women and children) in drone strike at altoQaeda summit'.
House of Khanadan Khan Dawar attacked in Mir Ali. Seven alleged militants killed and 4 injured. Car also destroyed in attack.
House of Khanadan Khan Dawar attacked in Mir Ali. Seven alleged militants killed and 4 injured. Car also destroyed in attack.
Van destroyed and 7 alleged militants killed near Mir Ali, North Waziristan.  Dead reported by some to be ?foreigners?.

Strike against mosque in Mir Ali, North Waziristan. 8 German alleged militants among dead ? case later reportedly leads to German intelligence withdrawing support from CIA. Benyamin E, ?Imran?, Fayyaz/ Bruseley, Gagreen Gill/ Siraj, Milton Smith/ Jamal, W
Double strike on 2 trucks in Mir Ali area kills up to 22 alleged TTP, including reportedly 5 local commanders: Zahid Mandev; Qari Barkatullah; Qari Monib; Fazal Amin; and Qari Ihsanullah.
Attack on alleged Haqqani Network compound kills 12 and injures 5 in Mir Ali, North Waziristan.
First Obama fatal strike kills 11to14 ? at least 5 'foreign militants' and 3to8 civilians, mostly of one family.  Zharki, Mir Ali,North Waziristan. CIA admits missing high value target.
3to5 killed in attack on house of alleged militant Nasimulah Khan in Spinwam, North Waziristan.
Up to 7 alleged militants died when CIA drones fired 6 missiles at a house. The attack took place hours after Pakistan ambassador to Washington again called on the US to halt drone strikes.
3to8 alleged militants killed and 3to4 injured in strike on house and vehicle. Kushali, North Wizaristan.
House of Munawar Jan destroyed in Zanani, North Waziristan. 5 alleged militants killed and 3 injured.
13to15 alleged militants killed in strike on car and house in Dre Nishatr, Shawal valley, North Waziristan.
9 alleged militants killed in strike on car. At least 1 civilian casualty. Datta Khel, North Waziristan.
Up to 9 alleged militants killed and 2to3 injured in a strike on two vehicles near Dogga.
4to5 alleged militants killed and 1 injured in a strike on a vehicle near Deegan.
4to5 alleged militants killed and several injured in a strike on a house in Datte Khel Kalai.
In an evening strike, CIA drones hit a house killing at least 17. This was the first strike since Pakistan retoopened its borders to Nato convoys after a seven month diplomatic standtooff.
Al Qaeda explosives expert Abu Musa altoMasri reportedly killed with 2 others in strike at Spalaga, North Waziristan. Attack hushed up for fear of unravelling local Taliban ceasefire.
4 alleged Afghan militants (or village residents)  killed in Spalga, North Waziristan. Car destroyed.
Al Qaeda planner Said altoSomali killed with 3 others, 3 injured, in attack on car in Aspalga, Miran Shah, North Waziristan.
6 alleged TTP militants killed and 5 injured in attack on house and car in Spalga, North Waziristan.

8to11 civilians or alleged militants reported killed and 10 injured in strike on house and car in Malik Ashdar, North Waziristan.  Earlier in day locals had fired on up to a dozen drones operating in the area.

Helicopter/air strike on a 'Pakistan Taliban facility' attacked by helicopters in which a drone observed and may have participated. Inital claims of 30 'Taliban' killed lowered to 8. This was denied by locals, who say dead were all woodcutters.
Vehicle destroyed in Darnashtra, South Waziristan. 3to5 alleged militants killed.
Attack with five drones destroys 2 houses, 2 cars in Dosali, North Waziristan. 15 killed including ?well known al Qaeda commanders? Abdullah Said al Libi and Zuhaib altoZahibi.

Second known strike outside FATA, probably aimed at Quetta Shura, kills al Qaeda's Abdullah Azzam al Saudi; and "at least" five others (including 2 "foreigners") Jani Khel, Bannu, NWFP . Provokes Pakistani outrage.
At least five killed including ?2 Arabs, 2 Pakistanis? in attack on Janni Khel, Bannu.
Strike injures Egyptian altoQaeda leader and ideologue Shaykh Issa altoMasri.

Attack on training facility of Hafiz Gul Bahadar (in peace deal with Pakistan) kills 11to14 militants, ?many Westerners, including US citizens.? CIA keeps details secret.  Kumsham, Miramshah, north Waziristan.
Up to 11 civilians, all part of same Mir Gul family, killed in Garyom, borders of North and South Waziristan.   Early reports claimed 5 'foreign militants' died.
Attack on alleged TTP camp kills 5to6 and wounds 4. Gariwam, North Waziristan.
Chased vehicle struck just as it parks at a house. Both destroyed. Razmak, North Waziristan. 4to6 killed, 3 injured.
Strike in Taaloo Ganj, Kurram Agency kills three and damages a nearby mosque.
TTP leader Hakimullah Mehsud and Al Qaeda bomb maker Abdul Basit Usman allegedly killed with 15 others in attack on Shaktoi, North Waziristan. Both emerge alive later.
Taliban commanders? meeting attacked.  At least 20 killed including Shahidullah, Hafiz Nizamuddin Storikhel, Khwarey and Mohtaj.

8to15 alleged militants killed and 3 injured in a strike on a vehicle in the Mandao borderlands area. Amongst dead was German citizen Samir H, believed to be one of the most dangerous Islamists in the country.
14 alleged TTP killed and 7 injured (including 5 civilians in nearby house). Car and housing compound destroyed. Shaktoi, South Waziristan.
Six killed in late night strike on Shaktoi, North Waziristan. TTP commander Punjab Azmatullah Mawiya reportedly killed.
13to22 killed an 6 injured in a strike. Bobar, South Waziristan.
17to22 killed and 6 reported injured in strike on two housing compounds in Babar Ghar.
Attack aimed at Taliban leader Baitullah Mehsud in his home town of Makeen. One killed.
Strike against alleged Baitullah Mehsud camp kills 7 including local TTP commander (Niaz Wali) and wounds seven. Makeen, South Waziristan.
Attack on alleged TTP training camp kills 14to16 and injures a further 10. Jangara, Makeen, South Waziristan.
8 killed (6 reported to be ?Arabs?), 5 wounded in attack on alleged militants in two cars that also destroys a house. Maken, South Waziristan. TTP stronghold.
10 killed, including possibly 5 civilians, in strike on van in Borvaika/ Gorwak in North Waziristan.
Up to 18 alleged militants killed in strike on compound in Gorvak/ Shawal, North Waziristan.
CIA drones attacked a compound in North Waziristan, killing up to 7 and injuring 3, according to local officials.
7 unknown alleged militants killed and 3 injured in a strike on a vehicle in the borderlands of North and South Waziristan.
Up to 10 killed and one injured in a strike. Disputes on wether the dead were militants or civilians.
At least 4 alleged militants killed when a drone struck a house in the late evening. The strike was reportedly targeting alleged militants linked to Hafiz Gul Bahadur.
Attack on closed madrassa occasionally used by TTP kills 0to5. Mantoi, South Waziristan.
Three alleged militants killed and two injured in attack on Kateera, Mir Ali, North Waziristan.

Attack on Maulvi Nazir's network kills '20 militants'. Haji Omar Khan aka Mohammed Omar falsely reported killed (Ob51 ? 31/12/09) . Two of his brothers and three nephews die; nearby homes damaged.  Mandata, South Waziristan.
Alleged militant training camp/ house destroyed and 14to21 people killed, Shakai, South Waziristan. Possible link of site to TTP commander Adam Khan.
Up to 25 killed and 5 injured at Taliban teenage suicide bomber training camp, Saam, near Ladha, South Waziristan.
Egyptian Khalid Habib, Al Qaeda's chief of external operations, killed in his parked vehicle along with 4 militants,  4 civilians, 7 injured. Tapargai, South Waziristan.
Uzbek militant Tahir Yuldashev allegedly killed with 7 others in attack at Tapar Ghai, Kanigram, South Waziristan. His militant IMU group deny death for more than a year.
Final strike of Bush presidency on abandoned girls' school kills 4 militants, injures several. Madin, South Waziristan. Part of Baitullah Mehsud's infrastructure.
Alleged TTP training camp attacked in Laddha, Karwan Manza, South Waziristan. 8to9 killed, 12 injured.

CIA fatally wounds TTP leader Baitullah Mehsud after multiple attempts.  Obama personally authorizes attack. 11 others also killed, including his second wife, uncle, father and mothertointolaw and 7 bodyguard.
Fivetovehicle convoy destroyed and 35to40 alleged TTP militants killed in Laddha, Karwan Manza, South Waziristan.
Attack on car kills al Qaeda planner Abu Sulayman altoJazairi and others. Nearby house badly damaged. Kaniguram, Wana, South Waziristan.
Up to 35 killed (including Uzbek militants, say Taliban) and 9 injured in strike on Zangari, South Waziristan.   First Obama strike against Pakistan Taliban (TTP) and leader Baitullah Mehsud.
Five militants, Pakistani and foreign, killed in strike on car in Ladha South Waziristan, say Taliban. Two ?spies? later murdered in retaliation for attack.

Seven killed, three injured in Baghar Cheena, South Waziristan.  Last available secret CIA report: ?a Predator killed 4to6 militants delivering rockets to a militant camp near the Afghan border and probably HVT Abu Ubaydh Al Tunisi.? No new records of his
4to5 killed, 4 injured in attack in Angor Ada/ Baghar, South Waziristan.  3 ?Arabs? possibly among dead.
Strike on house of TTPtolinked local kills 12 and injures 8 at ?militant training facility?. Sararogha, Wana, South Waziristan.
Four alleged TTP militants killed and 5 injured as they eat dinner. Landikhel, South Waziristan.
6to7 killed and 6 injured in attack on truck and motorbike allegedly crossing from Afghanistan.  Angor Adda, South Waziristan. House also attacked.
3to6 killed and 3to7 injured in strike on a compound. Angor Adda, South Waziristan.
5 killed, 6 injured in attack on local TTP commander in Saraogha, South Waziristan. Some report Kalimullah Mehsud dies in attack ? though likely killed that day by Pakistan forces.
Four alleged militants killed in attack on house/ compound in Zeba, South Waziristan. No further details known.
Attack on house and vehicle kills up to 25 in Tabbi Langhar Khel, South Waziristan. Taliban say only militants 5 dead.
8 alleged militants killed and 5 injured in Khand Morsak, first strike in South Waziristan in x weeks.  Possible ?bait? for Ob 130.
16to18 alleged militants killed in attack on Dwasarak, South Waziristan. ?Dozens injured?.
8to10 people killed in strike on religious school in Wacha Dana, South Waziristan.  7 civilians reportedly among dead in this or Obama 214.
Home of Zari Khan Shamsikhel destroyed. 8to9 killed, 2 injured. Shalam Ragzhai, South Waziristan. ?Some foreign militants? possibly among dead.
6 alleged militants killed in strike on ?hidetoout? in Laddha, South Waziristan.
Strike in Raghzai area, near Wana, South Waziristan reported by local security sources. Impact unknown.
No injuries as 4 car occupants escape into orchard before vehicle destroyed in Karez, South Waziristan.

At least five killed, including two ArabtoCanadians. Secretly CIA  claims ?strike killed Al Qaeda paramilitary operatives subordinate to Al Qaeda commander and East Africa Embassy bomber Usama Al Kini.?

An attack on a house and/ or car killed up to thirteen alleged militants, including ?foreigners?, and injured five. Three students ?with militant links? were killed in either this or Ob230, named as Hafiz Bilal, Waheed Ullah and Fayaz.
Twelve killed and 30 injured in major strike against Maulvi Nazir (wounded) in Kari Kot, Wana, South Waziristan.  Some reports of 'women and children' killed.
Strike on vehicle kills al Qaeda operational chief Usama altoKini and his lieutenant Sheikh Ahmed Salim Swedan, both linked to 1998 US African embassy bombings. Kari Kot, Wana, South Waziristan.
TTP communications centre attacked in Painda, South Waziristan, killing 3to5 people.
At least 3 killed, 5 wounded strike in Kari Kot, Wana, South Waziristan.  Strike 'causes huge fire in village, panicking residents'.
Hamza altoJufi, a longtotime Egyptian resident of Waziristan and alleged militant, killed with 6to9 others in Karikot, South Waziristan.
Fazal Karim?s house destroyed in Landidog, South Waziristan, killing 1to5 people ? possibly all civilian to and wounding 3.
3 Turkmenistan nationals and 2 ?Arabs? reported among 7 dead in attack on house/ compound in Azam Warsak, South Waziristan. Al Qaeda finance officer Abu Zaid altoIraqi later reported killed.
Attack on Haqqani Network kills 8to16 militants and civilians. Midtolevel altoQaeda leader Dr Arshad Waheed dies. CIA claims 'more altoQaeda trainees were killed'.
Five alleged members of Pakistan Taliban (TTP) killed in Wana, South Waziristan, in an attack attributed either to an IED or drone.
Attack on alleged militant house and truck in Wana kills 9to10 and injures 2.
3to6 killed in strike on a compound. Zeba Pahar, South Waziristan.
Seven killed, including 3 alleged 'foreigners' in attack on a house next to a madrassa in Azam Warzak, South Waziristan.
Compound attacked in Zoynari, South Waziristan.  15to23 ?suspected militants? killed.
First known fatal US drone strike inside Pakistan. Target was Nek Mohammed (linked to an assassination plot against General Musharraf), four other Taliban killed.
9to13 killed and several wounded in double strike. Two killed in first attack, then 10 rescuers killed when drone returned. Shah Alam, Wana, South Waziristan.
4 alleged militants killed in strike on car in Azam Warsak, South Waziristan.
Up to 4 killed and up to 2 injured in strike on a compound. Azam Warsak, South Wazaristan.
3to4 killed and 5 injured in strike on vehicle. Baghar, South Waziristan
4to6 killed and 3to4 injured in a strike on a vehicle. Azam Warsak, South Waziristan.
Up to 4 killed, 2 alleged militants and possibly 2 civilians in a strike in a vehicle in Khawashi Khel.
Up to 10 killed and 7to10 injured in a strike on a house where a Taliban funeral took place. Possible civilian deaths.

Rare attack on HezbtoitoIslami allegedly kills Taliban commander Abdul Rehman, Islam Wazir and 11to23 others. Bhagar, South Waziristan, (NB an Abdul Rahman killed along with 130 others in NATO Afghanistan airstrike 4/9/2009) Secret CIA report claims:?Predato
Attack on madrassa kills 12to13, eight of whom are reported militants. CIA secretly claims dead are 'foreign altoQaeda trainees'. Locals say some students killed.

Confused reports of attack on either bazaar, house, or funeral of victims of Ob129 kills 16 alleged militants, including Maulvi Nazir?s 2nd in command  Mullah Shamsullah. (NATO later reportedly kills Shamsullah in Afghanistan April 2011)  Azam Warsak, Sou
A vehicle damaged in Azam Warsak, South Waziristan. Some reports claim that 2to4 alleged militants are killed ? others that all are able to flee when a drone misses them.
9 killed ? possibly all civilians ? in attack on house linked to Baitullah Mehsud?s TTP. Sara Khwara, South Waziristan.

8to10 killed in attack in Zari Noor, Wana, South Waziristan.  Target possibly militant Yaqub Wazir, playing key role in peace agreements with Pakistan military. Secret CIA report claims ?multiple foreign Al Qaeda members and local associates? killed and in
Four killed, four injured in strike on an antitoaircraft truck in Shin Warzak near Wana, South Waziristan.
Al Qaeda?s Osama bin Ali bin al Dawsari and local Taliban leader, Omar Khaitab reported among dead in attack on Mizai Nara, South Waziristan.
Attack on alleged training facility run by TTP commander Noor Wali kills 17 and injures 35. Kokat Khel, South Waziristan.

Strike on seminary in Zeralita kills altoQaeda 'chemical weapons team': leader Abu Khabab altoMasri; Abu Mohammed Ibrahim bin Abi al Faraj al Masri, a religious leader; Abdul Wahhab altoMasri and Abu Islam altoMasri. 3 young boys killed. CIA apologises for co
3to4 killed and 2 injured in strike on house. Shin Warsak, South Waziristan

Attack on wrong house kills eight members of Malik Gulistan Khan's family, including Khan, three of his sons (youngest aged 3) and a cousin.  Dilfar, Wana, South Waziristan. CIA admits missing target.
Secret CIA paper identifies failed attack: ?a Predator attempted to target an Al Qaedatoassociated meeting but missed target. It did not cause collateral damage.? Gankikhel, South Waziristan.
Explosivestofilled trucks create fireball, killing 8 civilians (including women and children). Gangi Khel, Wana, South Waziristan.
Attack on alleged militant truck kills 4 but also destroys two nearby shops and wounds 5 civilians. Khel, Wana, South Waziristan.
Ilyas Kashmiri, Al Qaeda affiliate commander, reported killed along with Mohammad Usman, Ibrahim, Farooq, Amir Hamza and Imran.   Killed as they slept in an orchard, Ghwa Khwa, South Waziristan.
According to secret CIA report, ?A Predator killed four to 10 persons associated with Al Qaeda commander and logistician Abu Wafa Al Saudi?. Location unknown ? likely North Waziristan.
Possible drone strike in Tiarza area, South Waziristan. Single media source reports 5 dead ? no further reports.

A previously unreported strike revealed by a US official in August 2011. The official stated that the strike, one of two that day, ?killed a handful of militants, including a top A.Q. [al Qaeda] terrorist.? The Bureau is seeking details of the al Qaeda militant reported killed.
